(1 comment)

Thanks Juan - neat unit test.

In the the cache tests:

glance/tests/functional/test_cache_middleware.py

which start with the cache enabled

 self.api_server.deployment_flavor = "cachemanagement"

there is a test

test_cache_middleware_trans_v2_without_download_image_policy

which checks for a 403 in the cache enabled case.

How much work do you think it would be to create an equivalent test in the v2 image tests? Eg in:

v2/test_images.py

which start with the cache disabled:

self.api_server.deployment_flavor = 'noauth'

ie

[pipeline:glance-api-noauth]
pipeline = versionnegotiation gzip context rootapp

If it was possible we'd be able to ensure a 403 is returned in the non-cache case which I think would be a great regression test.

Let me know -- thanks.

Patch Set 8:

Ok, from testing it looks like for these functional tests changes to the policy file are not dynamically picked up, so the start_servers is needed.

It is possible to set the rules using the existing set_policy_rules function -- as long as it's done before the call to start servers, this worked for me:

        rules = {"context_is_admin": "role:admin", "default": "",
                 "download_image": "!"}

        self.set_policy_rules(rules)
        start_servers...
